cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with improving the performance of neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a solution to the problem of mistranslating rare words, which involves fixing the norms of vectors, and integrating a lexical module. These solutions involve optimization and training of the model, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approaches on eight language pairs, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, and may fall under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
